Given a [[vector bundle|Vector bundle]] $$E \to M,$$ a connection on $$E$$ is a bilinear map 

$$
\nabla\colon\mathcal X(M)\times\Gamma(E)\to \Gamma(E),\quad
(X,\sigma)\mapsto\nabla_X\sigma,
$$

which is $$\mathcal C^\infty(M)$$-linear in $$X$$ and satisfies a product rule for $$\sigma$$:

$$
\nabla_{fX} \sigma = f \nabla_X \sigma,\quad
\nabla_X(f\sigma) = (Xf)\sigma + f \nabla_X \sigma.
$$

We call $$\nabla_X \sigma$$ the //covariant derivative// of $$\sigma.$$

