!! In Coordinates

Let $$U$$ be a coordinate neighborhood for $$M^m$$ and a trivializing neighborhood for $$E$$ and let $$\partial_i,\ i=1,\dots,m$$ be a frame for $$\T M$$ and $$e_a,\ a=1,\dots,\rank E.$$ Then for $$X=\sum v^i \partial_i$$ and $$\sigma=\sum \sigma^a e_a$$ we have

$$
\nabla_X \sigma = \sum_{i,b} v^i \Bigl(
\partial_i\sigma^b+\sum_a \varGamma_{ia}^{\,b} \sigma^a \Bigr) e_b
$$

and any collection of smooth functions $$\varGamma_{ia}^{\,b}$$ describes a connection in this neighborhood.